In article <CL8rs8.AvG@eskimo.com>, Gideon Yuval <gideony@eskimo.com> wrote:
>Here's another human-factors issue:
>Maybe NSA can break IDEA, and maybe not. In any case, they won't
>expose their IDEA-breaking capability casually (say, to get some
>civil-forfeiture goodies off a porn seller) -- these guys were
>careful about such things since Purple!
> 
>If they can break Clipper, they can always break it first, get
>the key out of escr*w later, and nobody would be any the wiser.
> 
>It therefore seems that IDEA is _effectively_ stronger than Cliper
>-- in one case, the guys that can break it were born with masking-tape
>over their mouths.

Not all legal wiretaps are used as evidence in court. Some are only used to
gather leads which can produce hard independent evidence.

